<subSubSection id="FDAA651F063F2E73FF48FA3DFBF1223E" pageId="21" pageNumber="322" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B50F3694063F2E73FF48FA3DFBF1223E" blockId="21.[151,1437,1738,1945]" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86063F2E73FF48FA3DFED12266" bold="true" box="[199,315,1810,1836]" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">Remarks.</emphasis>
The carapace is about as wide as long, smooth, strongly domed, and abruptly convex behind frontal margin which resembles 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17063F2E73FE21FA18FDA5221A" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[430,591,1846,1873]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Cryptodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="322" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86063F2E73FE21FA18FDA5221A" box="[430,591,1846,1873]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">C. tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the rostral and anterolateral teeth are blunt. 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17063F2E73FBCCFA19FADF221A" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[1091,1333,1846,1872]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Cryptodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="322" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tumida">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86063F2E73FBCCFA19FADF221A" box="[1091,1333,1846,1872]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">Cryptodromia tumida</emphasis>
